title: Appointments to Hong Kong Council on Smoking and Health
content_text:
p>
    The Government gazetted today (August 20) the re-appointment of Ms Lisa Lau 
    Man-man as Chairman, and Mr Ma Siu-leung as Vice-chairman, of the Hong Kong 
    Council on Smoking and Health.  Meanwhile, the re-appointment of six serving members, namely Dr Amy Chan 
    Kit-ling, Mr Abraham Chan Yu-ling, Mr Chau Yui-chi, Ms Yolanda Ng Yuen-ting,

Mr Joseph Wan Kwok-hung and Ms Brenda Wu Shuk-yin, and the appointment of Ms 
    Celine Ho Ming-wai as the Council's new member, are also announced.  All the appointments will be effective from October 1, 2010.  Established in 1987, the Council is an independent statutory body to advise 
    the Government on matters related to smoking and health. It is also tasked 
    to advance public education concerning the effects of smoking on the 
    community and the individual as well as to engage in smoking-related

community and the individual as well as to engage in smoking-related research. The full membership of the committee is as follows: Ms Lisa Lau Man-man (Chairman)
